%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22868%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sarah%20Beran%20and%20Brooks%20Bell%2C%20the%20founders%20of%20Worldclass.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68385dbcc6ad288d14822559%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22651%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20Beran%20and%20Brooks%20Bell%2C%20the%20founders%20of%20Worldclass.%3Cp%3EWorldclass%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-risks-young-people-reduce-diet-alcohol-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMore%20young%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-know-about-colon-cancer-symptoms-diagnosis-chadwick-boseman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediagnosed%20with%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Part%20of%20why%20it's%20so%20difficult%20to%20diagnose%20is%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-colonoscopy-colon-cancer-symptoms-colorectal-oncologist-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20diarrhea%20and%20bloating%20can%20be%20caused%20by%20everything%20from%20hemorrhoids%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-misdiagnosis-young-people-ibs-gluten-allergy-symptoms-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egluten%20allergy%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20other%20hurdle%20is%20stigma%3A%20people%20just%20don't%20want%20to%20talk%20about%20seeing%20blood%20in%20the%20toilet%20or%20in%20their%20pencil-thin%20stools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20it's%20something%20that%20I%20see%20quite%20frequently%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Fola%20May%2C%20a%20gastroenterologist%20and%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20Medicine%20at%20UCLA%2C%20told%20BI.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20it's%20common%20for%20people%20to%20ignore%20and%20they%20may%20avoid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorectal-cancer-high-mortality-young-people-signs-symptoms-disease-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esharing%20their%20symptoms%3C%2Fa%3E%20out%20of%20embarrassment.%20%26quot%3BThey%20delay%20bringing%20it%20up%20until%20it%20gets%20more%20and%20more%20severe%2C%20and%20they%20actually%20can't%20function%20or%20have%20a%20normal%20workday%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20added.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20then%2C%20their%20cancer%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20progressed%20to%20later%20stages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dc18d645-de64-41b5-9de4-286bba25de41%5C%22%3EAnal%20bleeding%20is%20common%20with%20younger%20patients%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20colon%20cancer%20symptoms%20are%20easy%20to%20miss.%20Abdominal%20pain%20or%20constipation%20can%20be%20linked%20to%20many%20different%20conditions%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-stage-4-colon-cancer-symptoms-pain-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eceliac%20disease%20or%20IBS.%20%3C%2Fa%3EThat's%20why%20rectal%20bleeding%20is%20important%20to%20flag.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoshua%20Demb%2C%20a%20researcher%20who%20studies%20early-onset%20colon%20cancer%20and%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20San%20Diego%2C%20led%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2819248%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20most%20common%20symptoms%20of%20colon%20cancer%20in%20young%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemb's%20study%20found%20rectal%20bleeding%20was%20the%20most%20common%20sign%20of%20colon%20cancer%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20altered%20bowel%20movements%20or%20abdominal%20pain%20%E2%80%94%20because%20it%20was%20more%20specific%20and%20harder%20to%20explain%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-environmental-causes-microplastics-antibiotics-sleep-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elifestyle%20changes%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20know%20how%20seriously%20to%20take%20some%20symptoms.%20Anal%20bleeding%20is%20often%20caused%20by%20non-life%20threatening%20conditions%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fwhy-does-my-butthole-itch%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehemorrhoids%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20patients%20who%20are%20otherwise%20young%2C%20healthy%2C%20and%20who%20have%20no%20family%20history%20can%20be%20dismissed%20by%20doctors%2C%20partly%20because%20colonoscopies%20are%20more%20involved%20procedures%20and%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.goodrx.com%2Fconditions%2Fcolon-cancer%2Fcolonoscopy-cost%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20difficult%20work%20is%20making%20sure%20a%20symptom%20is%20%26quot%3Battributed%20to%20the%20correct%20condition%2C%26quot%3B%20Demb%20said%2C%20without%20preemptively%20scaring%20people%20or%20overlooking%20the%20early%20signs%20of%20colorectal%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c1f258d5-c987-48db-ae17-f32bbac8c3fe%5C%22%3EMillennials%20are%20afraid%20to%20talk%20about%20stool%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPoop%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fwhy-is-shitting-still-so-embarrassing%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20taboo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20regarded%20as%20unsanitary%20and%20embarrassing.%20As%20societies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ted.com%2Fpages%2Fwhy-are-we-so-awkward-about-poop-transcript%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVictorian-era%20England%3C%2Fa%3E%20developed%20indoor%20plumbing%20and%20individual%20latrines%20to%20replace%20communal%20ones%2C%20defecation%20became%20more%20private%20%E2%80%94%20and%20consequently%20more%20shameful%20to%20talk%20about%20in%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stigma%20has%20never%20really%20gone%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20interviewing%20colon%20cancer%20patients%2C%20Demb%20learned%20many%20young%20people%20are%20afraid%20to%20broach%20the%20topic%20of%20poop%20and%20rectal%20bleeding%20with%20their%20doctor%2C%20even%20though%20that%20conversation%20could%20be%20life-saving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPart%20of%20that%20apprehension%20comes%20from%20probably%20not%20having%20had%20to%20discuss%20this%20ever%20before%20in%20their%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20people%20enter%20their%2050s%20and%20colonoscopies%20become%20standard%20care%2C%20talking%20about%20bowel%20movements%20becomes%20slightly%20more%20normalized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Naik%C3%A9%20Vorbe%20started%20cycling%20through%20diarrhea%20and%20constipation%2C%20she%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20talk%20about%20it%2C%20and%20hesitated%20at%20first.%20%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20really%20speak%20about%20gastrointestinal%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20Vorbe%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20Haiti%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVorbe%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-years-of-stomach-pain-diagnosed-colon-cancer-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estage%203B%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2031.%20By%20then%2C%20her%20cancer%20had%20spread%20so%20much%20that%20she%20needed%20to%20have%20parts%20of%20her%20colon%20and%20liver%20removed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20composite%20image%20of%20a%20woman%20smiling%20and%20leaning%20on%20a%20table%20at%20a%20party%20and%20the%20same%20woman%20in%20a%20hospital%20bed.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6819203c3fe8d3928364f9e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENaik%C3%A9%20Vorbe%2C%2042%2C%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20stage%203B%20colon%20cancer%20after%20years%20of%20bowel%20issues.%3Cp%3ENaik%C3%A9%20Vorbe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Rodriguez%2C