%20de%20minimis%20shipping%20as%20part%20of%20its%20tariff%20program.%20That%20meant%20many%20companies%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-brands-reduce-tariff-costs-bonded-warehouse-de-minimis-ends-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epivot%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPortless'%20founder%20and%20CEO%2C%20Izzy%20Rosenzweig%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20had%20been%20preparing%20for%20the%20end%20of%20de%20minimis%20since%20last%20September.%20It%20raised%20its%20Series%20A%20with%20the%20understanding%20that%20de%20minimis%20would%20be%20ending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenzweig%20said%20that%20with%20tariffs%20disrupting%20global%20supply%20chains%2C%20Portless'%20pitch%20is%20resonating%20with%20many%20brands.%20By%20fulfilling%20orders%20outside%20the%20US%2C%20the%20company%20can%20help%20brands%20defer%20their%20duty%20payments%20until%20an%20order%20crosses%20the%20border%20on%20its%20way%20to%20a%20customer.%20Portless%20uses%20an%20informal%20entry%20process%20called%20Type%2011%20to%20import%20the%20goods%20to%20the%20US.%20It%20pays%20duties%20on%20behalf%20of%20its%20brand%20customers%2C%20who%20then%20pay%20Portless%20back%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20isn't%20a%20company%20in%20the%20US%20that%20isn't%20looking%20for%20a%20new%20way%20of%20doing%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenzweig%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20getting%20buried%20in%20inbound.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20%3Cspan%3Eimpacted%20by%20tariffs%20and%20the%20end%20of%20de%20minimis%20have%20also%20explored%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-brands-reduce-tariff-costs-bonded-warehouse-de-minimis-ends-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eother%20strategies%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20like%20storing%20inventory%20in%20bonded%20warehouses%20and%20foreign%20trade%20zones%2C%20to%20defer%20their%20duty%20payments%20and%20lessen%20the%20hit%20on%20their%20balance%20sheets%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Portless%20logo%20is%20shown%20inside%20its%20fulfillment%20center%20in%20Shenzhen%2C%20China%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6837470e6ffb6822ec61a769%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20look%20inside%20Portless'%20Shenzhen%20fulfillment%20center.%3Cp%3EPortless%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPortless%20typically%20works%20with%20mid-market%20brands%20earning%20between%20%245%20million%20and%20%24150%20million%20in%20annual%20revenue.%20Rosenzweig%20said%20brands%20of%20that%20size%20benefit%20the%20most%20from%20having%20better%20access%20to%20cash%2C%20which%20Portless%20helps%20with%20by%20fulfilling%20small%20orders%20by%20plane%20instead%20of%20tying%20up%20large%20amounts%20of%20inventory%20on%20shipping%20containers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20our%20model%2C%20it%20is%20like%20a%20live%20supply%20chain%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20reacting%20immediately%20to%20the%20demand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20customers%20include%20home%20wellness%20device%20brand%20Canopy%2C%20kids'%20clothing%20brand%20Andy%20%26amp%3B%20Evan%2C%20and%20apparel%20brand%20SA%20Fishing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22223e42d8-9dcc-4a78-b60f-12a72b13ec80%5C%22%3EBuilding%20a%20'supply-chain-as-a-service'%20company%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20creating%20Portless%2C%20Rosenzweig%20founded%20an%20online%20marketplace%20called%20Browze%20that%20sourced%20products%20directly%20from%20factories%20in%20China.%20In%20his%2010%20years%20running%20the%20company%2C%20he%20saw%20firsthand%20how%20complicated%20global%20supply%20chains%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Portless%20plans%20to%20use%20the%20funding%20to%20expand%20into%20new%20markets.%20It%20has%20a%20new%20fulfillment%20center%20in%20Vietnam%20and%20plans%20to%20open%20another%20in%20India%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20third%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20also%20plans%20to%20build%20more%20services%20to%20help%20brands%20improve%20their%20supply%20chain.%20It%20plans%20to%20introduce%20the%20ability%20to%20book%20quality%20control%20inspections%20through%20its%20customer%20portal%20within%20the%20next%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20today%20Portless%20is%20fundamentally%20changing%20cash%20flow%20with%20a%20new%20supply%20chain%20model%2C%20we%20want%20to%20simplify%20supply%20chain%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenzweig%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20things%20will%20change%20in%20our%20model%2C%20like%20small-batch%20manufacturing%2C%20and%20we'll%20be%20rolling%20out%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommerce%20Ventures%20partner%20Matt%20Nichols%20said%20the%20firm%20led%20Portless'%20Series%20A%20because%20it%20believes%20%26quot%3Bthat%20the%20'direct-ship-from-manufacturer'%20model%20will%20be%20the%20future%20for%20much%20of%20retail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20they%20invested%20with%20the%20assumption%20that%20the%20de%20minimis%20loophole%20would%20go%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20able%20to%20get%20comfortable%20by%20talking%20to%20many%20of%20Portless'%20customers%20and%20finding%20out%20that%20the%20tax%20advantage%20was%20not%20the%20reason%20they%20decided%20to%20choose%20Portless%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20all%20focused%20on%20aligning%20production%20volumes%20with%20actual%20demand%2C%20and%20this%20was%20the%20best%20model%20to%20facilitate%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amstone%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Emstone%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%40mlstone.04.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3