with%20significant%20market%20swings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStuck%20and%20unsure%20of%20my%20next%20move%2C%20I%20pause%2C%20take%20a%20breath%2C%20and%20decide%20to%20call%20up%20an%20expert%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fthebrentweiss%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBrent%20Weiss%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20certified%20financial%20planner%20and%20the%20cofounder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffacet.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacet%20Wealth%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EApril%2016%2C%202025.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20My%20main%20objective%20for%20the%20call%20is%20to%20figure%20out%20whether%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20transfer%2C%20but%20Weiss%20teaches%20me%20so%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20starts%20by%20telling%20me%20that%20my%20initial%20instinct%20to%20combine%20accounts%20was%20a%20good%20one.%20He's%20a%20fan%20of%20consolidation%20and%20believes%20that%20a%20simplified%20financial%20life%20is%20a%20healthy%20financial%20life.%20However%2C%20before%20starting%20any%20sort%20of%20consolidation%20process%2C%20such%20as%20an%20HSA%20transfer%20or%20a%20401(k)%20rollover%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20know%20everything%20about%20the%20new%20product%20you're%20opting%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hadn't%20even%20considered%20looking%20under%20the%20hood%20of%20Flores.%20Is%20it%20a%20good%20provider%20worth%20using%20as%20my%20primary%20HSA%20account%3F%20How%20does%20it%20compare%20to%20Ameriflex%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20could%20be%20notably%20different%2C%20he%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20an%20HSA%2C%20there%20is%20a%20big%20disparity%20in%20the%20quality%20of%20HSA%20providers%20within%20the%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20ask%20him%20what%20makes%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%26quot%3B%20HSA%20provider%2C%20and%20he%20points%20to%20two%20main%20factors%3A%20fees%20and%20investment%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20you%20also%20want%20to%20consider%20how%20you'll%20get%20your%20money%20out%20of%20the%20account%2C%20he%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BMost%20will%20send%20you%20a%20debit%20card%20you%20can%20use%20%E2%80%94%20the%20good%20ones%20will%20do%20that.%20The%20good%20ones%20almost%20operate%20like%20a%20good%20bank%20account.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20debit%20cards%20from%20Ameriflex%20and%20Flores%2C%20but%20that%20green%20flag%20was%20about%20to%20be%20overshadowed%20by%20a%20major%20red%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20soon%20as%20Weiss%20mentions%20fees%2C%20I%20start%20poking%20around%20on%20my%20Flores%20dashboard.%20It%20takes%20a%20bit%20of%20time%2C%20but%20I%20eventually%20find%20the%20investment%20account%20fee.%20It%20ranges%20from%200.4%25%20to%200.9%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222070%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hsa%20transfer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683743d46ffb6822ec61a6eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFlores%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20Weiss%2C%20who%20asks%20if%20I%20meant%200.04%25%20instead%20of%200.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNope.%200.4%25%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20say%2C%20quadruple-checking%20where%20the%200%20lies%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20decimal.%20%26quot%3BDoes%20that%20sound%20high%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20very%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20almost%20half%20a%20percent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeiss%2C%20who%20has%20an%20HSA%20account%20through%20Fidelity%2C%20says%20his%20account%20doesn't%20charge%20an%20investment%20fee%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plot%20thickens.%20When%20I%20find%20the%20annual%20fee%20I've%20been%20paying%20Ameriflex%2C%20it's%20even%20higher%3A%200.6%25!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B0.6%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20asks.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20very%2C%20very%20high.%20If%20I%20found%20out%20that%20I%20was%20being%20charged%200.4%20or%200.6%2C%20I%20would%20be%20upset%20about%20that.%20I%20would%20not%20use%20that%20provider.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20then%20refer%20to%20my%20recent%20transactions%20page%20to%20attach%20a%20dollar%20amount%20to%20the%20fee.%20Each%20quarter%2C%20I'm%20billed%20about%20%247%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221664%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hsa%20transfer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68374582ca50259add4d3583%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22594%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAmeriflex%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20less%20shocking%20figure%2C%20he%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20huge%20dollar%20amount%20today%20because%20of%20the%20size%20of%20the%20balance%20%E2%80%94%20so%20I%20want%20to%20be%20aware%20of%20that%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20overcomplicate%20things%20%E2%80%94%20but%20if%20the%20goal%20for%20people%20out%20there%20who%20are%20investing%20is%20to%20build%20a%20significant%20pot%20of%20money%20to%20use%20tax-free%20in%20the%20future%2C%20fees%20matter%20and%20they%20do%20add%20up%20over%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20lot%20to%20think%20about%2C%20and%20I%20haven't%20even%20asked%20him%20about%20uninvesting%20my%20funds%20yet.%20He%20does%20reassure%20me%20that%20it's%20standard%20procedure%3A%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20majority%20of%20HSAs%20you%20will%20have%20to%20sell%20it%20and%20then%20transfer%20that%20to%20the%20new%20company%20under%20the%20assumption%20the%20new%20HSA%20provider%20has%20investment%20options%2C%20then%20reinvest%20that%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20he%20says%20next%2C%20though%2C%20makes%20my%20brain%20spin%20even%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%2C%20you're%20in%20California.%20There%20are%20states%20that%20actually%20don't%20acknowledge%20or%20recognize%20HSA%20tax%20deferral%2C%20and%20I%20think%20California%20is%20one%20of%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explains.%20%26quot%3BSo%20there's%20actually%20a%20situation%20where%2C%20if%20you%20have%20a%20gain%20in%20that%20account%2C%20just%20know%20that%20there%20might%20be%20a%20reportable%20gain%20to%20the%20state%20of%20California%20in%20HSA.%20It's%20wild.%20I%20don't%20know%20why%20they%20do%20that%20and%20why%20it's%20so%20complicated%2C%20but%20it%20is%20a%20very%20nuanced%20rule%20for%20only%20like%20four%20or%20five%20states%20in%20this%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20final%20layer%20of%20complexity%20helps%20me%20reach%20my%20ultimate%20decision%20to%20abandon%20the%20transfer%2C%20at%20least%20for%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20benefits%20of%20consolidation%20%E2%80%94%20simplifying%20your%20financial%20life%20and%20not%20losing%20track%20of%20accounts%20%E2%80%94%20doesn't%20apply%20to%20me.%20I%20have%20a%20tidy%20spreadsheet%20dating%20back%20to%202015%20that%20tracks%20all%20of%20my%20account%20balances%2C%20including%20both%20HSAs%2C%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20the%20Ameriflex%20investment%20fee%20is%20larger%20than%20Flores%2C%20but%20with%20a%20relatively%20small%20balance%2C%20I'm%20fine%20eating%20the%20seven%20bucks%20a%20month%2C%20at%20least%20for%20the%20near%20future.%20I%20can%20always%20revisit%20the%20transfer%20option%20as%20the%20account%20grows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20also%20revisit%20another%20nifty%20strategy%20Weiss%20mentioned%3A%20Using%20a%20different%20HSA%20provider%20than%20the%20one%20offered%20by%20your%20company.%20I%20incorrectly%20assumed%20you%20were%20stuck%20with%20whichever%20provider%20your%20company%20elected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20go%20anywhere%20you%20want%2C%20set%20up%20your%20own%20HSA%20account%2C%20make%20your%20own%20contributions%20to%20it%20and%20deduct%20it%20on%20your%20tax%20returns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20That's%20exactly%20what%20Weiss%20does.%20He%20prefers%20Fidelity%20over%20the%20provider%20that's%20offered%20through%20his%20employer.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20do%20an%20electronic%20transfer%20once%20a%20year%20to%20make%20my%20annual%20contribution.%20I%20make%20sure%20it's%20listed%20on%20my%20tax%20return%20because%20it%20doesn't%20flow%20through%20my%20W-2%2C%20so%20I%20have%20to%20deduct%20it%20on%20my%20tax%20returns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20more%20complicated%20than%20simply%20electing%20a%20percentage%20of%20your%20paycheck%20to%20have%20your%20employer%20send%20straight%20to%20your%20HSA%2C%20and%20there's%20one%20catch%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20only%20downside%20is%20that%20if%20your%20income%20is%20under%20the%20Social%20Security%20wage%20base%2C%20you%20actually%20don't%20pay%20FICA%20tax%20on%20direct%20HSA%20contributions%2C%20so%20there%20can%20be%20a%20tax-savings%20on%20that%20contribution.%20But%2C%20if%20your%20income%20is%20over%20the%20Social%20Security%20wage%20base%2C%20then%20you're%20not%20really%20saving%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20by%20doing%20it%20on%20your%20own.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMay%2021%2C%202025.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20about%20a%20month%20of%20procrastinating%20and%20second-guessing%20my%20thought%20process%20and%20preliminary%20decision%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20move%20forward%2C%20if%20for%20nothing%20else%20than%20to%20finish%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20double%20down%20on%20the%20decision%20to%20pause%20the%20transfer%2C%20but%20not%20before%20tidying%20up%20a%20few%20loose%20ends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20I%20have%20funds%20sitting%20in%20my%20Ameriflex%20cash%20account%20that%20are%20eligible%20to%20invest.%20I%20transfer%20the%20maximum%20(about%20%24700)%20into%20the%20investment%20account%20so%20it%20can%20grow%20in%20the%20target%20date%20fund%20I'd%20selected%20last%20year%20when%20I%20opened%20the%20account.%20It's%20a%20bummer%20that%20the%20%24500%20minimum%20will%20just%20sit%20in%20the%20cash%20account%2C%20unable%20to%20grow%2C%20but%20I'm%20treating%20that%20money%20as%20a%20partial%20emergency%20fund.%20I%20still%20have%20the%20Ameriflex%20debit%20card%20and%20can%20use%20those%20funds%20for%20any%20medical%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Flores%2C%20I%20finally%20set%20up%20an%20investment%20account.%20I'd%20already%20hit%20the%20%241%2C000%20cash%20minimum%20and%20had%20about%20%24720%20eligible%20to%20invest%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221514%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hsa%20transfer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F683745c66ffb6822ec61a735%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221091%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFlores%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20Weiss'%20direction%2C%20I%20selected%20a%20self-directed%20investment%20account%20(0.4%25%20fee)%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20managed%20one%20(0.9%25%20fee).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20it%20was%20time%20to%20pick%20a%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeiss%20suggested%20a%20target-date%20fund%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20among%20the%2014%20fund%20options%20listed.%20I%20went%20with%20the%20Vanguard%20Total%20Stock%20Market%20ETF%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fetfs%2Fvanguard-total-stock-market-index-fund-etf-shares-us9229087690%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVTI%3C%2Fa%3E).%20I%20was%20also%20able%20to%20set%20up%20recurring%20transfers%20from%20the%20Flores%20cash%20account%20to%20the%20investment%20account%2C%20something%20I'd%20never%20figured%20out%20how%20to%20do%20with%20Ameriflex.%20Now%2C%20anytime%20my%20balance%20exceeds%20the%20%241%2C000%20cash%20minimum%2C%20the%20excess%20will%20be%20automatically%20sent%20to%20my%20investment%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20monitor%20both%20accounts%20semi-regularly%2C%20mostly%20to%20understand%20how%20much%20money%20I'm%20losing%20to%20fees%20in%20each.%20If%20the%20number%20ever%20becomes%20too%20high%20to%20stomach%2C%20I'll%20consider%20making%20an%20adjustment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20was%20tedious.%20I%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20poking%20around%20both%20sites%2C%20reading%20through%20the%20FAQs%2C%20and%20translating%20the%20fine%20print%2C%20but%20of%20all%20things%20to%20do%20due%20diligence%20on%2C%20HSA%20funds%20rank%20high.%20This%20money%20is%20a%20portion%20of%20my%20nest%20egg%2C%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWeiss%20assured%20me%20that%20I'm%20likely%20not%20the%20only%20one%20who%20has%20struggled%20with%20an%20HSA-related%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHSAs%20are%20young%20and%20still%20figuring%20things%20out%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20just%20crossed%20over%20their%2021st%20birthday.%20They%20were%20created%20in%202003%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20tech%20savvy%2C%20they're%20not%20clean%20user%20experiences%2C%20they're%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20why%2C%20for%20HSAs%2C%20it's%20really%20important%20to%20understand%20what%20you're%20getting%20into.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealth-savings-account-hsa-transfer-funds-process-taxes-investments-fees-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748509202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6837427bca50259add4d34f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealth-savings-account-hsa-transfer-funds-process-taxes-investments-fees-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20process%20of%20transferring%20my%20HSA%20funds%20was%20more%20complex%20than%20I%20imagined%2C%20but%20left%20me%20with%20a%20key%20takeaway%3A%20Pay%20attention%20to%20fees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealth-savings-account-hsa-transfer-funds-process-taxes-investments-fees-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Smokey%20Robinson%20files%20%24500m%20case%20against%20rape%20accusers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A17485082810